cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.AI

This paper is primarily focused on cost-effective big data clustering, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with the computational aspects of clustering, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of cloud computing, which could place it under cs.DB (Databases) or cs.DC. Finally, the use of regression models to optimize the clustering process could also classify the paper under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
